Hi, I have a vector, x and z which 21 length long and a array, N which 21*21*4001 size. Now when I tried to plot a filled contour with `contourf(vec(x), vec(z), Z[:,:,1])` I get an error: `attempt to save state beyond implementation limit
contours not sorted in ascending order
GKS: Rectangle definition is invalid in routine SET_WINDOW
Error showing value of type Plots.Plot{Plots.GRBackend}:
ERROR: InexactError: trunc(Int64, NaN)` Is there anything I am doing wrong here and how can I resolve it? Thanks
